OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1772467873
OL,3,CCouncil tax in Dumfries and Galloway
OL,4,Cto increase by 8.5%
OL,6,FCouncillors in Dumfries and Galloway
OL,7,Fhave voted to increase council tax by
OL,8,F8.5%.
OL,10,FThey backed the Labour group's budget
OL,11,Fby one vote, rejecting the SNP
OL,12,Fadministration's proposal, which
OL,13,Fincluded an 8% rise.
OL,15,FLabour is the third largest group at
OL,16,FDumfries and Galloway Council, behind
OL,17,Fthe Conservatives.
OL,19,FTheir budget includes #67,000 to
OL,20,Freinstate bins in lay-bys and #300,000
OL,21,Ffor play parks.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/6
