OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1772467873
OL,3,CCouncil tax in Dumfries and Galloway
OL,4,Cto increase by 8.5%
OL,6,FIt also proposes #2.7m of savings
OL,7,Fincluding a 20% cut to the funding for
OL,8,Fthe Citizens Advice charity which
OL,9,Fsupports people with financial and
OL,10,Fhousing issues.
OL,12,FSpeaking to ITV Border, council leader
OL,13,FStephen Thompson said: "It's not ideal
OL,14,Fbut it's an interesting feature that
OL,15,Fno administration of this council term
OL,16,Fhas been able to take forward its own
OL,17,Fbudget proposal.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1772467873
OL,3,CCouncil tax in Dumfries and Galloway
OL,4,Cto increase by 8.5%
OL,6,F"We have to accept the nature of the
OL,7,Fcouncil is that we have a look of
OL,8,Fdifferent groups different proposals
OL,9,Fand we have to respect the fact the
OL,10,Fbudget that won on the day is the
OL,11,Fcouncil budget and we have to take it
OL,12,Fforward."
OL,14,FThe council said the council tax
OL,15,Fincrease was to help protect front
OL,16,Fline services and to invest in "key
OL,17,Flocal priorities.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
